TIRESIAS, OR LEGACY-HUNTING.

THIS practice is touched in passing in Epp. 1. 1. 77. It is described in Cicero, Paradox 5. 2 ‘An eorum servitus dubia est, qui eupiditate peculii nnllam con- ditionem recusant durissimae servitutis? Hereditatis spes quid iniquitatis in ser- viendo non suscipit? quem nutum locupletis orbi senis nou observat? Loquitur ad voluntatem: quidquid denunciatum sit, facit: assectatur, assidet, muneratur.¹ The ‘orbitas' which was the temptation to it belongs to that disinclination to marriage and its responsibilities which was a marked feature of Roman life. See notes on Od. 4. 7. 19, C. S. 18—20.
